text:
Kismet is a city in Seward County, Kansas, United States. In 2010, 459 people lived there.
History.
The first post office in Kismet was created in November 1888.
Geography.
Kismet is at (37.205043, -100.701081). The United States Census Bureau says that the city has a total area of. All of it is land.
2010 census.
The 2010 census says that there were 459 people, 145 households, and 115 families living in Kismet.
Education.
Kismet is a part of USD 483 Southwestern Heights. The district high school, Southwestern Heights, is between Kismet and Plains. The Southwestern Heights High School mascot is Southwestern Heights Mustangs.
Kismet High School was closed because of school unification. The Kismet High School mascot was Kismet Pirates.
